  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Aarti, I'm Miss Maya. How was your sleep last night?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Not so good. Woke up too early. My exam is coming up, and I feel so tired."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds tough. Sleep loss before exams is rough. How are you managing your revision time these days?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I try to study early morning, but my mind is so slow. Also, I can't focus for long. Kahi nahi lagto."
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get that, your brain needs rest to work well. Sometimes a short break helps more than long hours. Have you tried the Pomodoro method, 25 minutes study, 5 minutes rest?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Pomodoro? No, I don't know that. How does it work?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "The Pomodoro method is simple: study for 25 minutes, then take a 5 minute break. After four cycles, take a longer break. It helps keep the mind fresh. Would you try it today?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Maybe. But I need to finish this chapter today. If I don't start now, I'll fall behind."
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get that pressure. Starting is the hardest part. Maybe try one Pomodoro cycle first, 25 minutes focused, then a break. How does that sound?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm. Maybe I can try one cycle. But I need to stay on schedule. Okay, let's give it a shot."
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Good! One cycle at a time. What chapter are you working on? Maybe we can talk about it during your break."
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Chapter on cardiology. Very tough. Too many diagrams and terms. Break sounds nice. I'll take it."
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That’s a relief. Cardiology can be heavy with all those diagrams and terms. During your break, what’s one thing you like to do to recharge?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Maybe a cup of tea. Or I just sit quiet for a bit. Can't do much else right now. Need to get back to study. Thanks for the chat."
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're welcome, take that break, Aarti. A quiet moment or tea sounds perfect. I'm here when you're ready. Good luck with your chapter!"
    }
  ],
